      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIFE GETS BETTER (1) finished seventh at Young two runs back then performed admirably last time out, making up plenty of ground but being denied by a narrow margin over 1760m at Junee. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Meets a comparable field and she can take this out. SPREAD THE FEAR (8) finished third at Riverina Paceway two starts back then was highly competitive at her latest appearance over 1760m at Junee, beaten only a head into second after being close to the pace throughout. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. Good enough to put herself in the winners' stall. MASTABLASTA (2) is in the mix following a respectable third at his most recent appearance over 1758m at Leeton. ARKLOW (9) is worth some thought despite her last-start seventh over 1760m at Junee on March 31.",
